    "Background": {
      "text": "AKA Acute myelogenous leukemia or non-lymphocytic leukemia\nMost common acute leukemia in adults (around 80% of cases)\n65 yo median age of diagnosis, Male:Female 5:3\nCharacterized by clonal proliferation of myeloid precursors(blast cells >20% in the periphery)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Presents with symptoms of:\nAnemia\n:\nweakness\n, easy\nfatigability\n,\nSOB\nNeutropenia\n: infections\nThrombocytopenia\n: gingival bleeding/\nenlargement\n, ecchymoses,\nepistaxis\n,\nmenorrhagia",
